						               													<description>Grim Forge is a drafting game played over seven rounds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First you draft the hero cards that will be summon during the game. After that, each round you draw one mana card to place in front of you, and then you go to the Summoning for that round. In this round you use the mana cards you've collected so far to summon a hero.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When summoning a hero, you place them face down in front of you and pointed at another player. All heroes are revealed simultaneously and have one of three effects: they can steal points from the player they point at, they can steal from the neighbors of the player they point at, or they can deflect incoming attacks to the player they point at.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After seven rounds whoever has the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
